Since `a` converges to `La`, for any `ε > 0`, there exists an `N` such that for all `n ≥ N`, `|a n - La| < ε`. This implies `La - ε < a n < La + ε`. Therefore, `a n ≤ La + ε`. Since this holds for all `n ≥ N`, and `a` is monotone, we can conclude that `a n ≤ La` for all `n`.

